\sqrt{399} = 19.975
dV = dR + dR + dR = 3dR
dV/3 = dR
1\%/3 = dR
 V = \frac{4}{3} \pi R^3 \Rightarrow dV = 4\pi R^2 dR \Rightarrow \frac{dV}{V} = \frac{4\pi R^2dR}{\frac{4}{3} \pi R^3} \le .01 \Rightarrow \frac{3dR}{R} \le .01 \Rightarrow \frac{dR}{R} \le \frac{1}{300} \Rightarrow \max{\left(\frac{dR}{R}\right)} = \frac{1}{300} 
